46
00:04:58,157 --> 00:05:01,909
[singing a lullaby]

47
00:05:01,911 --> 00:05:03,661
[baby cooing]

48
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,828
[singing]

49
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:15,981
[truck approaching]

50
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:18,500
[truck honking]

51
00:05:18,502 --> 00:05:20,803
Señora, do you
need help?

52
00:05:26,327 --> 00:05:28,160
[with Japanese accent]
Aguayo?

53
00:05:28,162 --> 00:05:30,754
Aguayo?

54
00:05:30,756 --> 00:05:32,022
We can take you there.

55
00:05:33,258 --> 00:05:35,568
[baby fussing]

56
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:43,200
This is our daughter,
Esperanza.

57
00:06:01,637 --> 00:06:02,678
[Chester]: Get her inside!

58
00:06:04,215 --> 00:06:05,139
What happened?

59
00:06:05,141 --> 00:06:07,199
Yuko found us.

60
00:06:07,201 --> 00:06:09,368
She's taken Luz
and the baby.

61
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:10,961
- What?
- Let's get her to bed.

62
00:06:10,963 --> 00:06:11,770
- We'll find her.
- Let's go bring her inside.

63
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:14,206
Hector,

64
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:15,816
can we borrow your truck?

65
00:06:15,818 --> 00:06:17,151
Yes, yes, of course.

66
00:06:17,153 --> 00:06:18,711
Why don't I
come with you?

67
00:06:18,713 --> 00:06:20,237
Stay with
your grandmother.

68
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:38,413
Chester, watch out
for military tonight.

69
00:06:38,415 --> 00:06:40,082
It's no place
for Japanese folks

70
00:06:40,084 --> 00:06:41,658
so close to Los Alamos.

71
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:44,403
Did something happen tonight?

72
00:06:44,405 --> 00:06:45,971
In the war?

73
00:06:47,424 --> 00:06:49,642
Do you know
where Hiroshima is?

74
00:07:03,348 --> 00:07:05,282
[speaking in Japanese]

75
00:08:08,489 --> 00:08:10,505
[radio broadcast]:
<i>8:15 a.m. local time,</i>

76
00:08:10,507 --> 00:08:12,099
<i>the United States
detonated a bomb</i>

77
00:08:12,101 --> 00:08:14,751
<i>over the Japanese port city
of Hiroshima.</i>

78
00:08:14,753 --> 00:08:16,419
<i>This is reportedly
the largest bomb</i>

79
00:08:16,421 --> 00:08:18,831
<i>ever detonated
in human history.</i>

80
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:20,666
[tuning the radio
to another station]

81
00:08:20,668 --> 00:08:23,518
<i>♪ ...be just dandy ♪</i>

82
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:28,298
<i>♪ The day I take my Candy ♪</i>

83
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:31,601
<i>♪ And make her mine, all mine ♪</i>

84
00:08:31,603 --> 00:08:33,245
[♪♪♪]

85
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,211
[Chester]: Luz...

86
00:08:43,207 --> 00:08:44,715
Luz!

87
00:08:49,697 --> 00:08:50,596
Yuko-san?

88
00:08:51,623 --> 00:08:53,098
[speaking in Japanese]

89
00:09:04,636 --> 00:09:05,944
Oh, my god...

90
00:09:08,974 --> 00:09:10,899
Luz...

91
00:09:10,901 --> 00:09:13,643
The <i>yurei.</i>

92
00:09:13,645 --> 00:09:14,720
She's taken him.

93
00:09:14,722 --> 00:09:16,413
Where did she take him?

94
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:18,791
In the car.

95
00:09:25,157 --> 00:09:26,298
[speaking in Japanese]

96
00:09:43,267 --> 00:09:44,149
[Asako gasps]

97
00:09:53,777 --> 00:09:56,620
[soft humming]

98
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,859
[humming]

99
00:10:02,861 --> 00:10:04,503
[baby cooing]

100
00:10:37,321 --> 00:10:40,205
[baby cooing]

101
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:04,396
[passersby laughing]

102
00:11:07,777 --> 00:11:09,259
The whole world's
falling apart,

103
00:11:09,261 --> 00:11:12,095
and people
are celebrating.

104
00:11:12,097 --> 00:11:13,505
As though a child
in Hiroshima

105
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:15,282
had anything to do
with this war.

106
00:11:20,939 --> 00:11:24,458
I wanted
revenge once.

107
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:26,627
It consumed me.

108
00:11:26,629 --> 00:11:30,631
I thought getting it
would ease things,

109
00:11:30,633 --> 00:11:34,176
but I didn't feel
any better.

110
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:41,124
Major Bowen
want to kill you.

111
00:11:41,126 --> 00:11:43,977
It was either him or you.

112
00:11:45,964 --> 00:11:49,983
You did only
thing you can.

113
00:11:49,985 --> 00:11:51,634
But I didn't...
How did you...

114
00:11:51,636 --> 00:11:52,444
Shh!

115
00:11:53,897 --> 00:11:56,615
Only our own people know.

116
00:11:58,226 --> 00:11:59,701
It's all right.

117
00:12:00,979 --> 00:12:05,574
If WRA not find out by now,

118
00:12:05,576 --> 00:12:07,584
they never will.

119
00:12:10,322 --> 00:12:11,338
You see...

120
00:12:13,417 --> 00:12:19,162
it easy to want vengeance.

121
00:12:19,164 --> 00:12:20,806
Natural as death.

122
00:12:24,186 --> 00:12:27,062
What about you?

123
00:12:28,599 --> 00:12:31,024
I cry more tear

124
00:12:31,026 --> 00:12:33,268
come back from camp

125
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:37,698
than at camp.

126
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,534
All we had...

127
00:12:40,536 --> 00:12:44,037
gone.

128
00:12:44,039 --> 00:12:46,856
Gone.

129
00:12:46,858 --> 00:12:48,625
Give him to me.

130
00:12:48,627 --> 00:12:51,194
Give me my baby!

131
00:12:51,196 --> 00:12:52,329
We will stay
with her.

132
00:12:52,331 --> 00:12:54,006
Don't worry.
Go find the baby.

133
00:12:56,402 --> 00:12:57,551
I'm going now.

134
00:12:57,553 --> 00:12:59,778
I'll get him back.

135
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:01,221
I'm coming.

136
00:13:01,223 --> 00:13:02,055
I'm coming with you!

137
00:13:02,057 --> 00:13:03,281
Lie back.

138
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:05,559
Chester will get him.

139
00:13:10,215 --> 00:13:11,439
You haven't called
the police?

140
00:13:11,441 --> 00:13:12,840
About the couple
in the car?

141
00:13:12,842 --> 00:13:13,716
No, no.

142
00:13:13,718 --> 00:13:14,693
Good.

143
00:13:15,887 --> 00:13:17,362
I need you to
take me back there.

144
00:13:41,897 --> 00:13:43,597
Was there anyone else
in the car?

145
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:45,840
Just them.

146
00:13:45,842 --> 00:13:48,018
[girl sobbing nearby]

147
00:13:50,255 --> 00:13:51,979
[sobbing]

148
00:13:51,981 --> 00:13:55,758
[sobbing]
I didn't do it...

149
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:56,610
I didn't do it.

150
00:13:59,690 --> 00:14:02,950
It was the woman,

151
00:14:02,952 --> 00:14:04,368
with... with the baby.

152
00:14:05,937 --> 00:14:10,182
We'll take you
to a doctor, okay?

153
00:14:10,184 --> 00:14:13,085
Can you please
tell me what happened first?

154
00:14:15,856 --> 00:14:16,813
[baby cooing]

155
00:14:16,815 --> 00:14:21,009
[speaking in Japanese]

156
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:45,534
[clock ticking]

157
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:08,432
[♪♪♪]

158
00:15:09,743 --> 00:15:12,594
It was a good day,
wasn't it?

159
00:15:12,596 --> 00:15:14,246
Yes.

160
00:15:14,248 --> 00:15:16,857
It was.

161
00:15:16,859 --> 00:15:19,609
It's nice to keep your mind
on other things.

162
00:15:30,039 --> 00:15:32,097
Asako-san...

163
00:15:32,099 --> 00:15:34,949
I would like
some more broth.

164
00:15:34,951 --> 00:15:36,376
Yes, of course.

165
00:15:36,378 --> 00:15:38,253
Right away.

166
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:44,694
What are you
doing?

167
00:16:51,777 --> 00:16:52,869
[speaking in Japanese]

168
00:18:10,014 --> 00:18:11,031
[photographer
clearing throat]

169
00:18:29,885 --> 00:18:33,019
[flashbulb pops]

170
00:18:33,021 --> 00:18:34,971
[crickets chirping]

171
00:18:36,892 --> 00:18:39,284
[brakes squeak]

172
00:18:39,286 --> 00:18:40,393
[engine stops]

173
00:19:05,303 --> 00:19:06,219
Stay back.

174
00:19:06,221 --> 00:19:08,830
I'll go in
myself.

175
00:19:08,832 --> 00:19:10,740
Then what?

176
00:19:10,742 --> 00:19:12,425
She'll just give you the baby?

177
00:19:12,427 --> 00:19:15,428
My baby isn't Taizo.

178
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:18,006
The baby she wants
is from 25 years ago.

179
00:19:18,008 --> 00:19:20,249
Do you still have
the picture on you?

180
00:19:20,251 --> 00:19:21,601
I haven't forgotten it.

181
00:19:21,603 --> 00:19:23,603
I just need you to do it.

182
00:19:49,464 --> 00:19:50,371
She must have
hidden here

183
00:19:50,373 --> 00:19:52,132
for months.

184
00:19:52,134 --> 00:19:53,091
Preparing.

185
00:19:54,945 --> 00:19:56,694
[Chester]: Carving stones,

186
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:58,638
waiting for the baby to come.

187
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,974
Sutras on the walls...

188
00:20:00,976 --> 00:20:03,368
No.

189
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:06,871
Not sutras.

190
00:20:06,873 --> 00:20:09,274
Names.

191
00:20:17,159 --> 00:20:19,242
Her ancestors.

192
00:20:20,403 --> 00:20:23,555
Your ancestors.

193
00:20:23,557 --> 00:20:25,206
Dozens of them.

194
00:20:26,618 --> 00:20:28,585
She's preparing for a burial.

195
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,824
I have to go. Now.

196
00:20:34,826 --> 00:20:36,067
Go where?

197
00:20:36,069 --> 00:20:37,510
The limestone quarry.

198
00:20:37,512 --> 00:20:39,328
The stones are from
the other side of the woods.

199
00:20:39,330 --> 00:20:40,780
I know the path from here.

200
00:20:40,782 --> 00:20:42,740
No, listen, boy.

201
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,184
There's a better way.

202
00:20:44,186 --> 00:20:45,352
We just need some time.

203
00:20:45,354 --> 00:20:47,354
There is no time.

204
00:20:47,356 --> 00:20:49,764
She's taken my child.

205
00:20:49,766 --> 00:20:52,025
Now, please,

206
00:20:52,027 --> 00:20:55,320
promise me you'll give
the picture to Luz's <i>abuela.</i>

207
00:21:00,944 --> 00:21:02,118
God damn you.

208
00:21:05,599 --> 00:21:07,207
[door shuts firmly]

209
00:21:07,209 --> 00:21:09,084
[footsteps running away]

210
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:19,869
[Luz]: The trees
in the photo of you in Japan.

211
00:21:19,871 --> 00:21:22,037
[Asako]:
They're the same as here.

212
00:21:22,039 --> 00:21:24,349
[Luz]: She's here, I know it.

213
00:21:26,228 --> 00:21:28,395
[Asako]: How much farther?

214
00:21:28,397 --> 00:21:30,288
[baby cooing]

215
00:21:30,290 --> 00:21:32,899
[singing a lullaby]

216
00:21:37,722 --> 00:21:39,489
[speaking in Japanese]

217
00:22:15,685 --> 00:22:18,403
[distant singing]

218
00:22:37,023 --> 00:22:37,922
Yuko-san.

219
00:22:39,209 --> 00:22:41,259
[baby cooing]

220
00:22:45,790 --> 00:22:47,640
[speaking in Japanese]

221
00:23:43,014 --> 00:23:45,949
[Henry speaking in Japanese]

222
00:23:52,006 --> 00:23:53,289
[putting shotgun down]

223
00:24:16,731 --> 00:24:18,690
Pop, no!

224
00:24:22,796 --> 00:24:24,612
Find Ma! We need
another picture.

225
00:24:25,907 --> 00:24:27,056
[cocking shotgun]

226
00:24:27,058 --> 00:24:27,782
[firing]

227
00:24:30,603 --> 00:24:31,327
[firing]

228
00:24:33,990 --> 00:24:35,306
[baby crying]

229
00:24:35,308 --> 00:24:37,733
[groaning]

230
00:24:37,735 --> 00:24:39,669
[baby crying]

231
00:24:41,072 --> 00:24:43,423
Hold this.

232
00:24:43,425 --> 00:24:46,092
Do not let go.

233
00:24:47,654 --> 00:24:49,654
A sutra?

234
00:24:49,656 --> 00:24:50,388
Why?

235
00:24:55,478 --> 00:24:57,312
Pop, no, she'll possess you.

236
00:25:18,627 --> 00:25:20,701
[baby cooing]

237
00:25:20,703 --> 00:25:22,353
We tried that
at camp.

238
00:25:22,355 --> 00:25:23,463
It didn't work.

239
00:25:23,465 --> 00:25:24,522
It did work.

240
00:25:24,524 --> 00:25:25,423
[wheezing]

241
00:25:25,425 --> 00:25:27,191
It trapped her.

242
00:25:27,193 --> 00:25:28,860
Until we burnt it off.

243
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:30,194
Now, go!

244
00:25:30,196 --> 00:25:31,712
Get out of here.

245
00:25:31,714 --> 00:25:33,890
[wheezing]

246
00:25:37,512 --> 00:25:38,394
[Henry screams]

247
00:25:39,463 --> 00:25:40,688
[gasping]

248
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,235
Aah!

249
00:25:47,489 --> 00:25:49,322
[Henry]: Chester!

250
00:25:49,324 --> 00:25:51,199
Run!

251
00:26:03,730 --> 00:26:04,671
[cocking shotgun]

252
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:06,798
[firing]

253
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,093
[baby crying]

254
00:26:16,518 --> 00:26:18,351
[cocking shotgun]

255
00:26:24,359 --> 00:26:25,191
[firing]

256
00:26:29,030 --> 00:26:30,588
[gasping]

257
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:32,514
[Chester crying out]

258
00:26:32,516 --> 00:26:35,017
[gasping]

259
00:26:35,019 --> 00:26:36,619
[groaning]

260
00:26:45,104 --> 00:26:47,964
[straining]

261
00:26:50,719 --> 00:26:52,301
[crying out]

262
00:26:54,222 --> 00:26:55,963
[baby crying]

263
00:26:55,965 --> 00:26:58,433
[Chester groaning in pain]

264
00:27:00,228 --> 00:27:02,103
[baby crying]

265
00:27:05,233 --> 00:27:07,316
[Chester screams in protest]

266
00:27:24,827 --> 00:27:28,963
[speaking in Japanese]

267
00:27:32,819 --> 00:27:33,968
No!

268
00:27:38,377 --> 00:27:40,933
[birds singing]

269
00:27:54,449 --> 00:27:55,615
[Chester groaning in pain]

270
00:27:55,617 --> 00:27:56,449
[Luz]: Chester!

271
00:27:57,693 --> 00:27:58,934
[Chester]: The grave.

272
00:27:58,936 --> 00:28:00,119
She went in the grave!

273
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:09,128
Oh, my god...

274
00:28:12,542 --> 00:28:13,466
Henry.

275
00:28:14,544 --> 00:28:15,301
Henry!

276
00:28:17,138 --> 00:28:18,620
[sobbing]

277
00:28:18,622 --> 00:28:20,031
Hen...

278
00:28:20,033 --> 00:28:21,808
Henry!

279
00:28:23,661 --> 00:28:24,960
[speaking in Japanese]

280
00:28:24,962 --> 00:28:26,604
Henry!

281
00:28:28,041 --> 00:28:28,898
[sobbing]

282
00:28:33,046 --> 00:28:34,779
[sobbing]

283
00:28:36,065 --> 00:28:36,948
Come on.

284
00:28:43,723 --> 00:28:44,413
[sobbing]

285
00:28:52,823 --> 00:28:54,257
[Chester]:
